##  7. Git & Collaboration Flow

### ğŸª´ Branch Structure

| Branch      | Purpose                                     |
| ----------- | ------------------------------------------- |
| `main`      | Stable demo-ready version                   |
| `develop`   | Active development branch                   |
| `feature/*` | Feature work (e.g., `feature/deposit-form`) |
| `fix/*`     | Bug fixes                                   |
| `chore/*`   | Setup, config, docs                         |

###  Workflow

```bash
# Pull latest
git checkout develop
git pull origin develop

# Create new feature
git checkout -b feature/deposit-form

# Commit work
git add .
git commit -m "feat(deposit): add DepositPage and DepositForm"

# Push branch
git push -u origin feature/deposit-form
```

Open a **Pull Request** â†’ merge into `develop`.
After testing â†’ merge `develop` â†’ `main`.

###  Commit Convention

| Type        | Meaning            |
| ----------- | ------------------ |
| `feat:`     | New feature        |
| `fix:`      | Bug fix            |
| `refactor:` | Code restructuring |
| `docs:`     | Documentation      |
| `chore:`    | Config or cleanup  |

---

##  8. Completion Checklist

Before merging any feature PR:

* [ ] ESLint & Prettier checks pass
* [ ] Component split follows **Containerâ€“Presentation** pattern
* [ ] API handled via **TanStack Query**
* [ ] State handled via **Zustand**
* [ ] Toasts shown on all actions
* [ ] Screenshots attached to PR
* [ ] Reviewed & approved by one teammate

